  <heading>INDEX (immediate, scalar)</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Create index starting from immediate and incremented by general-purpose register</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction populates the destination vector by setting the first element to
the first signed immediate integer operand and monotonically incrementing
the value by the second signed scalar integer operand for each subsequent element.
The scalar source operand is a general-purpose register in which only the least significant bits corresponding to the vector element size
are used and any remaining bits are ignored. This instruction is unpredicated.</para>
    </authored>
    <predicated>False</predicated>
  </desc>
